reviews.text: What a fun place to eat! The service was amazing. Fun atmosphere. There was a piano/stage. No sure when they have live music but it would be fun to be there when they do! Food was delicious. The Delicatto pizza seemed like a strange combination of ingredients but was absolutely delicious!

A great place for authentic Brazilian food.  Delicious, savory, and a wide variety of Brazilian favorites. We went with a large group and they accommodated us well. We sampled lots of goodies, highly recommended!

No matter how you slice it, it's the best pizza in town.  It's perfect for that after the movie snack.  If it's Saturday, stop by & say Hi.  Staff will give you their best million dollar smile & pizza that will make you think you're back overseas on holiday again.

Amazing, delicious Brazilian food. We were craving some Brazilian snacks. we got the cochinas, pao de queso, passion fruit mousse, and fried plantains. It was delicious! it was my child's birthday and we got a free dessert too! The staff are amazing. They only had a few people working so there was a bit of a wait.

They had a lot of terrific Brazilian specialties that felt very authentic. Especially the street food. Probably the best pastel I've had. While Brazil isn't known for their pizza, they do have their own take on it, and this place does a great job recreating it. If you are familiar with Brazilian pizza and just want to taste one again, this a good spot. They even have ketchup and mayo on the table, which are traditional condiments for a lot of the dishes on the menu. The Italian Margherita pizza was pretty good too. It is lovely that they baked the margherita pizza to well done.
The Brazilian appetizers shined brightest. Very large menu, this place has much more than pizza. We look forward to going back and trying more items.

editorial_summary.overview: Wood-fired pizza, Italian food & gelato are found at this warm counter-serve with indoor fig tree.

detailedReviews.author: Julian Gonzalez
detailedReviews.text: Everything was just ok. Visited here while in town for work and unfortunately was slightly disappointed. Both my coworker and I came in when the place was pretty empty. We were seated right away and from the moment our drink orders were taken, things were a bit strange. She didn't confirm my drink choice and just brought me the same thing as my coworker. When we ordered our main entree, the picanha parmigiana, we thought we were good. We both ordered the same thing, thinking the concept of Brazilian-Italian food sounded interesting enough so it should be delicious. Unfortunately, when our orders came out, we were brought chicken parmigiana instead. I'm not usually one to complain but I wanted to let the server know about the mistake. Unfortunately we were met with resistance and told that no, that is what we ordered. She even stated she repeated the order twice which both my coworker and I confirmed she did not. We didn't pursue it any further and just clarified we'll eat it but to make sure we weren't charged for the more expensive dish. When she passed by the next time she did bring by a dessert to share at no charge I'm guessing to make it right. Maybe it was the expectation of wanting the picanha, but I didn't enjoy my meal as much. Oh well, you live and you learn. Our receipts reflected the correct prices so we paid for our meals and we left. Still haven't tried Brazilian-Italian cuisine, perhaps some day.

detailedReviews.text: My niece and I discovered a delightful restaurant after an exciting zipline adventure over Deer Creek. The bright, welcoming atmosphere and the friendly smiles of the staff set the perfect tone. Our lovely waitress, Susana, took care of us as I enjoyed a build-your-own plate with Yuka, fried plantain, and moist salmon‚Äîjust like I remembered from South America! We even met the co-owner‚Äôs daughter and the entire family, making us feel truly at home. The service was fast and professional, and the heartwarming backstory of the owners made our experience even more special. We can‚Äôt wait to return for more delicious meals and pastries!

detailedReviews.author: Sarah Hamilton
detailedReviews.text:
An impromptu date night led us here, and I definitely want to come back! The service was so quick and friendly, and the food was absolutely delicious. Their garlic focaccia reminded me of the one I had in Italy, and I craved fresh straciatella to dip it in. Instead, they had an awesome red sauce (which my husband ate because tomatoes and I don't get along.) Then, I had their Brazilian steak picanha, and the hubs had pasta. We were stealing bites of each other's food and ooohing the whole time!
I appreciated that as our movie time crept closer, the server was extra quick to help us get out the door.
I'm dying to go back for their desserts because we ran out of time. So so good, you guys. Definitely stop by and try it!

detailedReviews.text: Delicatto provides the best Brazilian & Italian pizza.
